Title: spatialDLPFC_Visium_spe
Description: SpatialExperiment object at the spot-level for the spatialDLPFC human brain (DLPFC) spatial transcriptomics data (n = 30) from the Visium platform from 10x Genomics generated by the Lieber Institute for Brain Development (LIBD) and available through the spatialLIBD Bioconductor package.

Title: spatialDLPFC_Visium_example_subset
Description: SpatialExperiment object at the spot-level for the spatialDLPFC human brain (DLPFC) spatial transcriptomics data (n = 30) from the Visium platform from 10x Genomics generated by the Lieber Institute for Brain Development (LIBD) and available through the spatialLIBD Bioconductor package. Subsetted to just 3 samples with only the lowres images for example purposes.

Title: spatialDLPFC_Visium_pseudobulk_spe
Description: Pseudo-bulked SingleCellExperiment object (SpatialExperiment object without spatial data) at the Sp09D spatial domain resolution for the spatialDLPFC human brain (DLPFC) spatial transcriptomics data (n = 30) from the Visium platform from 10x Genomics generated by the Lieber Institute for Brain Development (LIBD) and available through the spatialLIBD Bioconductor package.

Title: spatialDLPFC_Visium_modeling_results
Description: List of modeling results at the Sp09D spatial domain resolution for the spatialDLPFC human brain (DLPFC) spatial transcriptomics data (n = 30) from the Visium platform from 10x Genomics generated by the Lieber Institute for Brain Development (LIBD) and available through the spatialLIBD Bioconductor package.

Title: spatialDLPFC_Visium_SPG
Description: SpatialExperiment object at the spot-level for the spatialDLPFC human brain (DLPFC) spatial transcriptomics data (n = 4) from the Visium Spatial Proteogenomics (Visium-SPG) platform from 10x Genomics generated by the Lieber Institute for Brain Development (LIBD) and available through the spatialLIBD Bioconductor package.

Title: spatialDLPFC_snRNAseq
Description: SingleCellExperiment object for the spatialDLPFC human brain (DLPFC) single nucleus transcriptomics data (snRNA-seq, n = 19) from the Chromium platform from 10x Genomics generated by the Lieber Institute for Brain Development (LIBD) and available through the spatialLIBD Bioconductor package.
